cheatsheet

• + : together 
• - : then

search and replace in all lines : :%s/search/replace/g
-- remove % the replace only in line

go to previous edited file : ctlr+6 or :e#
split previous edited file : :sbp

toggling errors window : ctrl+t

toggle tree view : ctrl+\

comment out things:
toggle line comment(If the topmost selected line is commented, all selected lines are uncommented and vice versa.) : \-c-space
just adds a comment sign at the start of the line(works in visual mode) : <leader>-c-c
Same as cc except that the commented line(s) are yanked first : <leader>-c-y
Comments the current line from the cursor to the end of line : <leader>-c-$
lets you add a comment at the end of line : <leader>-c-A
removes comment signs(opposite of <leader>-c-c) : <leader>-c-u
